The benefit may cover visits for chiropractic care, acupuncture, naturopathic care, and massage therapy. The amount you pay for visits to alternative care providers varies by the type of service. You may choose from alternative care providers throughout our service area.* Some services may require a referral to receive care. Check your EOC for plan specifics. When you need alternative care, just choose a provider from the list provided here or at chpgroup.com , and call for an appointment. You can also call the Washington State Department of Health at 360-236-4700 or visit the Oregon Medical Board website at oregon.gov/omb/pages/index.aspx for additional information on alternative care certifying agencies/bodies, including malpractice history and disciplinary actions. You pay the charges listed on your EOC benefit summary directly to the provider. Some services are not covered even if ordered by the provider. Exclusions and limitations apply even if your plan covers the service when it is ordered by a participating provider. For more information and a complete listing of exclusions and limitations, see your EOC or contact Member Services. An e-visit is an online medical consultation with a Kaiser Permanente advice nurse that's available at no cost for select medical conditions such as nausea/vomiting, pink eye, female UTI, sore throat, sinus issues, constipation, and diarrhea.For questions or more information, you may contact Member Services via kp.org. iiiProvider selection criteria Kaiser Foundation Health Plan of the Northwest (KFHPNW) offers several networks that are comprised of the Kaiser Permanente integrated health care delivery system. The primary contracted provider groups and facilities that participate include: Northwest Permanente, P .C., Physicians and Surgeons, facilities owned and operated by Kaiser Foundation Hospitals (hospitals, Kaiser Permanente medical offices, Kaiser Permanente pharmacies), The Portland Clinic, The CHP group, and contracted hospitals. In general, the networks contain physicians, specialists and facilities to provide services to individuals and groups covered under all Kaiser Permanente plans. Prior to allowing network participation, providers must successfully complete the initial credentialing process and demonstrate their ongoing ability to meet credentialing standards through a re- credentialing process. Providers are required to provide the information needed to review and verify their credentials. To ensure quality and safety of care between re-credentialing cycles, Kaiser Permanente performs ongoing monitoring of the participating provider's performance. Kaiser Permanente acts on important quality or safety issues in a timely manner by taking appropriate action against a participating provider when occurrences of poor quality are identified. We also monitor and analyze member feedback relating to network access, availability of providers, and cultural needs and preferences. This information helps guide our network improvement efforts. If you are looking for a gender affirming treatment provider and can't find a provider close to you, please call our Member Services department at 1-800-813-2000 for help finding an in-network provider.Tiered network criteria in Oregon and Washington Kaiser Foundation Health Plan of the Northwest offers three tiered networks, including Added Choice, Added Choice + Dental Choice, and PPO Plus. The primary contracted provider groups and facilities that participate in Tier 1 include: Northwest Permanente, P .C., Physicians and Surgeons, facilities owned and operated by Kaiser Foundation Health Plan (Kaiser Permanente Medical Offices and Pharmacies), Kaiser Foundation Hospitals (hospitals), The Portland Clinic, and contracted hospitals. The Added Choice and Added Choice + Dental Choice networks are comprised of the Kaiser Permanente integrated health care delivery system (as described above) and The CHP group as Select Providers, and First Choice Health PPO Network (or First Health Network for members in states other than OR, WA, ID, MT, WY, ND, SD and AK) as PPO Providers. The Added Choice networks are designed to allow members access to all that Kaiser Permanente offers plus the option to seek care from providers outside our network. Select Providers can be located on kp.org and chpgroup.com . PPO Providers can be located at choiceproducts-northwest.kaiserpermanente.org/ added-choice . All other providers are considered Non-participating Providers and facilities. The PPO Plus network is comprised of the Kaiser Permanente integrated health care delivery system (as described above) and First Choice Health PPO Network (or First Health Network for members in states other than OR, WA, ID, MT, WY, ND, SD and AK) as PPO Providers. All other providers are considered Non-participating Providers and facilities. The PPO Plus network is designed to offer access to a broad provider network that includes both Kaiser Permanente providers and a nationwide network. Kaiser Permanente providers can be located on kp.org and PPO providers can be located at choiceproducts-northwest.kaiserpermanente.org/ppo-plus .
